If from one side it seems that there is an experimental vaccine capable of reducing mortality from Ebola, from the other it has not yet been found any drug that has clearly demonstrated to be suitable for the treatment of the existing infection.
A cocktail of antibodies, ZMapp, initially appeared promising on the field, but formal studies have revealed an inferior efficacy compared to that expected in the prevention of deaths.
