The USA Gymnastics supports the letter of the U.S. Olympic Committee and recognizes the absolute need of the Olympic community to work to create a safe environment for all its athletes.
We agree with what the USOC has stated, that is, that the interests of our athletes and our clubs, and their sport, can be better served by pursuing a significant change within our organization, and not with decertification.
USA Gymnastics has commissioned an independent investigation to determine how an abuse of the magnitude described with such courage by those who have survived Larry Nassar was able to remain hidden for so long, and is prepared to implement any necessary or appropriate changes.
USA Gymnastics and the USOC have the same goal: to make gymnastics and other sports as safe as possible, so that athletes can pursue their dreams in a reliable, positive and responsible environment.
In the course of the 1960s, Brzezinski was the advisor of John F. Kennedy and subsequently of the administration of Lyndon B. Johnson.
In the course of the 1976 elections, he advised Carter in matters of foreign policy before taking on the role of National Security Advisor (NSA) from 1977 to 1981, succeeding Henry Kissinger.
In his capacity as a member of the NSA, he collaborated with Carter on the diplomatic management of international affairs, including the Camp David Accords of 1978, the normalization of relations between China and the United States at the end of the 1970s, the Iranian Revolution (which led to the Iran hostage crisis in 1979) and the Soviet invasion of Afghanistan in 1979.
