This not only confirms that some dinosaurs had feathers, a theory already widely disseminated, but provides more details than the fossils, such as color and three-dimensional arrangement.
. According to what scientists say, the plumage of this animal was marrone castano in the upper part, with a pallida or carotenoide coloration in the lower part.
The discovery also allows to obtain detailed information about the evolution of bird feathers.
Because the plumage of the dinosaur is not equipped with the basic structure, the so-called rachis, but has instead other typical characteristics of feathers, barbs and barbules, the researchers have concluded that the rachis is probably the result of a subsequent evolutionary development of these characteristics.
The structure of the plumage suggests that it was not used for flight, but rather for temperature regulation or courtship. The researchers hypothesize that, although it is the tail of a young dinosaur, the specimen shows an adult plumage and not the down of a chick.
According to the researchers' hypotheses, although the tail belongs to a young dinosaur, the specimen reveals the plumage of an adult and not that of a chick.
An autobomb exploded yesterday morning in the police headquarters of Gaziantep, in Turkey, killing two agents and injuring more than twenty people.
The governor's office reported that among the injured, 19 were police officers.
The police reported that the suspect responsible for the attack is a presumed militant of Daesh (ISIL).
They have discovered that the functioning of the Sun is based on the same basic principles as those of other stars: the activity of all the stars in the solar system is determined by nothing other than their luminosity and rotation.
The luminosity is used together with the rotation to define the Rossby number of a star, which is related to the plasma flow.
The lower the number of Rossby, the lower is the activity of the star compared to the magnetic inversions.
