The 802.11n standard can operate both in the 2.4Ghz band and in the 5.0Ghz band.
Since the base station has dual radios, this will allow it to be backwards compatible with 802.11a, 802.11b and 802.11g.
The speeds of 802.11n are significantly higher than those of the previous versions, with a maximum theoretical throughput of 600 Mbps.
